#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn7.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Upāsakavagga "
msgstr "2. Lay Followers "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Bhikkhakasutta "
msgstr "20. A Beggar "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn7.20:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.20:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhikkhako brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then a begging brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.20:1.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho bhikkhako brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn7.20:1.4"
msgid "“ahampi kho, bho gotama, bhikkhako, bhavampi bhikkhako, idha no kiṃ nānākaraṇan”ti? "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, both you and I are beggars. What, then, is the difference between us?” "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn7.20:2.1"
msgid "“Na tena bhikkhako hoti, "
msgstr "“You don’t become a beggar "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.20:2.2"
msgid "yāvatā bhikkhate pare; "
msgstr "just by begging from others. "

# NOTE: See BB for readings.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.20:2.3"
msgid "Vissaṃ dhammaṃ samādāya, "
msgstr "Someone who has accepted domestic responsibilities "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.20:2.4"
msgid "bhikkhu hoti na tāvatā. "
msgstr "has not yet become a mendicant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.393, sc3
msgctxt "sn7.20:3.1"
msgid "Yodha puññañca pāpañca, "
msgstr "But one living a spiritual life "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.20:3.2"
msgid "bāhitvā brahmacariyaṃ; "
msgstr "who has shunned both good and bad, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.20:3.3"
msgid "Saṅkhāya loke carati, "
msgstr "having considered, they live in this world: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.20:3.4"
msgid "sa ve bhikkhūti vuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "that’s who’s called a mendicant.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn7.20:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhako brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the begging brahmin said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn7.20:4.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! … "

msgctxt "sn7.20:4.3"
msgid "upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
